| Module            | Purpose                                                | Sample Usage / Notes                                                                                                                                            |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| dnf / yum         | Install/remove/update packages on RHEL/CentOS 9        | `yaml\n- name: Install Nginx\n  ansible.builtin.dnf:\n    name: nginx\n    state: present`                                                                      |
| apt               | Install/remove/update packages on Debian/Ubuntu        | `yaml\n- name: Install Git\n  ansible.builtin.apt:\n    name: git\n    state: present\n    update_cache: yes`                                                   |
| systemd / service | Start, stop, enable, disable services                  | `yaml\n- name: Ensure nginx is running\n  ansible.builtin.systemd:\n    name: nginx\n    state: started\n    enabled: yes`                                      |
| copy              | Copy static files from control node to remote hosts    | `yaml\n- name: Copy nginx config\n  ansible.builtin.copy:\n    src: ./files/nginx.conf\n    dest: /etc/nginx/nginx.conf\n    mode: '0644'`                      |
| template          | Deploy dynamic configuration files using Jinja2        | `yaml\n- name: App config\n  ansible.builtin.template:\n    src: templates/app.conf.j2\n    dest: /var/www/myapp/config/app.conf\n    mode: '0644'`             |
| user              | Manage users and their attributes                      | `yaml\n- name: Create deploy user\n  ansible.builtin.user:\n    name: deploy\n    shell: /bin/bash\n    groups: sudo\n    state: present`                       |
| file              | Manage files/directories (create, delete, permissions) | `yaml\n- name: Create log dir\n  ansible.builtin.file:\n    path: /var/log/myapp\n    state: directory\n    owner: deploy\n    group: deploy\n    mode: '0755'` |
| git               | Clone/update Git repositories                          | `yaml\n- name: Clone repo\n  ansible.builtin.git:\n    repo: 'https://github.com/org/myapp.git'\n    dest: /var/www/myapp\n    version: main`                   |
| shell / command   | Execute shell commands on remote hosts                 | `yaml\n- name: Run migration\n  ansible.builtin.shell: "python manage.py migrate"\n  args:\n    chdir: /var/www/myapp`                                          |
| cron              | Schedule recurring tasks                               | `yaml\n- name: Daily backup\n  ansible.builtin.cron:\n    name: "Daily backup"\n    minute: "0"\n    hour: "2"\n    job: "/usr/local/bin/backup.sh"`            |

